-- Japanese Sold Net 862.6 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2013-04-24T23:53:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-24/japanese-sold-net-862-6-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended April 19 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 862.6 billion yen ($8.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 27.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 45.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 935.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 199.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 27.9 billion yen in stocks, and sold 195.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 422.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
